        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down House | Orpington Kent<ref target="#foot.f1"/></placeName>
                    <date>June 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1843</date>
                    <salute>My dear Hooker<ref target="#foot.f2"/></salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Yours to hand thanks for the information received I have sent you the notes on Volcanic Islands for your inspection when you have read them kindly return them to me as I must rewrite and correct them I have been very busy since I came here it seems to suit me here and I am now determined to show the people the gift of mankind in regards penmanship of a unusual kind which they seldom see</p>
<p>Believe me | Yours Faithfully | C Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">An address CD never used. This letter is either a copy made by an inaccurate copyist who interpolated details or a forged CD letter.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">If this is a copy of a genuine CD letter then ‘Hooker’ must be a mistranscription. CD would not have addressed <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2367.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Jackson Hooker</ref> so familiarly, and his son, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2357.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Joseph Dalton Hooker</ref>, had not yet returned from the <hi rend="italic">Erebus </hi> voyage. The addressee was possibly <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2392.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Leonard Horner</ref>, who would have been interested in the notes on volcanic islands. CD worked on <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8001.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Volcanic islands</hi></ref> during 1843 (see ‘Journal’; <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence </hi></ref> vol. 2, Appendix II).</note>
        </div>        
            
